title: Southern Lehigh's Nina DeLuna defeats Easton's Elessa Jacobs for Class AAA tennis title
text:
By Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 12, 2015 4:11 PM, updated October 12, 2015 5:23 PM View/Post Comments 
Nina DeLuna (Southern Lehigh) def. Elessa Jacobs (Easton) 6-4, 6-2 â€” Rapid Recap 
Southern Lehigh junior Nina DeLuna defeated Easton freshman Elessa Jacobs 6-4, 6-2 in the District 11 Class AAA tennis singles final on Monday afternoon at Lehigh University. 
Turning point : DeLuna took the final four games of the first set to turn a two-game deficit into a 6-4 set victory. 
What it means : The Spartan wins her second straight title after winning the championship in her first high school tennis season last year with a 6-0, 6-0 victory over Liberty's Samantha Peterson. The Red Rover shows she has a very promising career ahead of her as she gave the defending champion a battle.
